Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:06.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ōhama Beach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.64,0:00:06.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We've arrived at Ōhama Beach, which is two hours by car from Beika Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:14.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Old man Kogoro suddenly decided he wanted to go surfing, and thinking that trying to stop him would be hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.71,0:00:16.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{"Surf Shop Seagull", "Surfing School - Beginners Welcome" (half obscured, good job Porygon)}Ran and I ended up reluctantly tagging along.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.49,0:00:20.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hold the wetsuit tightly, and put your feet in as if you were stepping forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.83,0:00:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. If it was loose, water'd get in!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:42.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The one who started it all was this woman that he recently met, who invited him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:42.48,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Nagisa Imaoka (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put more strength into it!{TMS surfboard :D}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make sure you don't lose track of your surfboard, attach it to your ankle with the leash.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.58,0:01:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its length is slightly longer than the surfboard itself:\Nabout 2 meters for adults, and 1.5 meters for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.41,0:01:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't it get cut off?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, very rarely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.34,0:01:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if a big wave comes and tosses you about, there's no telling what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.39,0:01:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though that's what's fun about surfing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.54,0:01:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's go ride the waves!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.79,0:01:56.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Vivid summer memories surpass their season to solve mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:02:00.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A single figure laying on a sandy beach with no footprints in sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.26,0:02:01.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.92,0:02:04.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.00,0:02:06.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was out buying stock, so I'm late to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been looking forward to having the great detective Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:16.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,ever since Nagisa told me you were coming. I'm Kaishirō Imaoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:16.26,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kaishirō Imaoka (60)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for taking care of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.55,0:04:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even though it's my first\Ntime surfing, it was really fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.22,0:04:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the type of guy who likes to ride the waves, so I'm a great surfer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:30.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}More like the type who likes to ride on your ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.91,0:04:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even now, we're wasting time here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.88,0:04:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm itching to go surfing again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.22,0:04:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey mister, is this a tide calendar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.76,0:04:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Ah, that's right, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at this, it'll be spring tide tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.67,0:04:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Ōhama Beach here is famous due to the big variances between high tide and low tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:05:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At high tide at night, the coastline'll be about 100 meters closer than it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.80,0:05:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when the morning comes, the waves recede as if running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.71,0:05:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A wide, empty beach washed blank by the waves extends for more than a kilometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.57,0:05:18.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fun to wake up early and run around leaving footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I know just how you feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.43,0:05:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like finding a place nobody's stepped on when it's snowing, and going psssst—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.94,0:05:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are these trophies yours{, lady}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.85,0:05:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was quite a surfer in the amateur world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.86,0:05:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No surprise to me. Ah, I'm jealous that you have such a wonderful daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.58,0:05:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit embarrased to say it, but she's not my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.75,0:05:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me she's actually your son? She's a man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, she's my wife{can also mean in-law}. My bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:06:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh... B-Bride?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you're married to him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's 35 years between our ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.35,0:06:12.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't sink into the sea in depression, old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.84,0:06:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dad, let's keep surfing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.84,0:06:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I don't care anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:27.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so tired all of a sudden... So she was married, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's just us, Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.02,0:06:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, shall we get going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.40,0:06:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard in the car that there's a high-pressure front coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.78,0:06:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the waves. They're starting to have whitecaps!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that surfing was more fun when there were some waves though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people think so, but not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.18,0:07:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you two are beginners, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many people lose their lives getting snatched up by high waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.85,0:07:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must never take the sea lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll never enjoy surfing if you keep being such a wimp!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.40,0:07:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine, I'll be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be full of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.33,0:07:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can you do to stop high waves!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of your arrogance!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.95,0:07:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.19,0:07:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize I was shouting, I do apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.29,0:07:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The high-pressure front'll probably be gone by morning. At least wait until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really... Doesn't he have a challenger's spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's turned into an old geezer who lives for plastic models!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.30,0:07:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's no fun at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:07:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.87,0:08:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sea's calling "come and get me"!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.45,0:08:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In here, the restless blood of a surfing maiden is burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.54,0:08:13.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see what kind of marriage this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we can't go surfing, how about we go back to the boarding house{pension}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Left, left... No, no, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.22,0:08:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Urgh... There! Ahhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, so Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a customer at that shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.15,0:08:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Yeah, from what the owner of the boarding house{pension} said,\Nshe came here frequently to conquer the waves here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.70,0:08:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agh... And then three years ago they conquered her instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.44,0:08:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes? Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.67,0:09:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.46,0:09:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Your wife's gone missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.19,0:09:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, while I was in the kitchen preparing for tomorrow, she disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought she might have gone to visit you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she hasn't been here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me she went out in the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.67,0:09:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about her surfboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.90,0:09:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.72,0:09:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could she have taken one of the boards from the stock?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.89,0:09:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she could have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.18,0:09:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When looking at rough seas like today's, her eyes narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.15,0:09:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a shark chasing its prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.15,0:09:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister, something's shining in your breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it the new message light on a mobile?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.14,0:09:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from Nagisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.28,0:09:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sorry for not saying anything.\NAt karaoke. Might stay all night."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.22,0:09:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.53,0:09:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good thing she didn't go to the sea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if she's a shark, she can't\Ndo any surfing at a karaoke bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.09,0:10:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. But leaving without saying a word...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.23,0:10:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't get what she's thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The troubles of keeping a younger wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This shouldn't have happened" has become a catchphrase between us lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The high-pressure front went away at dawn, and the tide's all the way out at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.55,0:10:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the beach nice and clean, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.69,0:10:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.52,0:10:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Driftwood?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.20,0:10:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it someone wearing a wetsuit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:10:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.63,0:11:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.21,0:11:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too late, she's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.91,0:11:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:16.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Ran, contact the police.\NKid, bring Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just to be careful, bring some cardboard or something to spread around the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.81,0:11:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.19,0:11:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you manage to control your surfing maiden blood...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:40.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is most likely a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:45.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the only footprints around the corpse are ours, from running over to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.32,0:11:49.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just how did the killer do it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.40,0:12:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa... Nagisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.30,0:12:10.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:12.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sand?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.29,0:12:14.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would it be there...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.87,0:12:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.81,0:12:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? This guy's Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.45,0:12:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he appears on TV a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get his autograph later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.55,0:12:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.43,0:12:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you figured anything out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.33,0:12:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... To be frank, this was an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.86,0:12:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, so it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.88,0:12:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Seeing the rough seas brought by a high-pressure front, she probably couldn't bear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.55,0:12:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she sent a fake e-mail saying she'd gone to karaoke to her husband, Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,secretly put on one of the suits her workplace had in stock,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and with a board from the stock in hand,\Nwent out to the sea via the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wonder why Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't wear her own wetsuit which is hanging there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.83,0:13:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably thought I'd spot her from the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.80,0:13:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing that if I did, I would've stopped her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa... really loved surfing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.25,0:13:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.11,0:13:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when she was enjoying surfing, she got tossed about by the high waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.98,0:13:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the momentum wound Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s leash around her neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the waves pulled the board away, and as a result, her neck was strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the marks from the cord on her neck are inside her wetsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.60,0:14:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.86,0:14:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was facing stormy seas!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.60,0:14:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cord could've got inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.25,0:14:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the suits are meant to be skin-tight so that water doesn't get in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.42,0:14:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so noisy, geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go away, you brat!{Hey! [whoosh whoosh] Kid, go over there!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, with her board missing, Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was returned to this beach, to the place of her lover, Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.43,0:14:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So perceptive! That's a sharp mind at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Look at Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s toenails.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.73,0:14:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right... maybe she went out to sea while she was putting on a pedicure?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:42.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where have I seen that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.21,0:14:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! It's Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s on the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:55.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Those bags!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:09.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This really was a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:11.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.89,0:15:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Footprints left by someone over 100 kg?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.87,0:15:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Like, if someone weighing 60 kg carried someone weighing 50 kg on their back, they'd leave deep footprints, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what this is about, but anyway, when we came, the beach was clean, with nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess you're right. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:50.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn it! He {\i1}has{\i0} to be the killer, so how did he carry the corpse out to the beach? {there's only one suspect, so no need for "that person"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:52.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I can't figure that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:16:00.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What? Was it crushed by something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:03.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Crushed... by something...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.36,0:16:16.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I'm right...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.99,0:16:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:31.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Embraced by the waves, Nagisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.81,0:16:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, she began her journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.42,0:16:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I think!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.71,0:16:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.50,0:16:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is what I'd like to say, but this was a murder case made to look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Murder case?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.01,0:17:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.35,0:17:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the toenails on Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s left foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.96,0:17:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was applying a pedicure, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.08,0:17:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it odd she would go to the sea while painting her nails?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.77,0:17:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.52,0:17:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was odd too when Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} mentioned it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for why she did, it was because she had to stop halfway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, while applying her pedicure...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.34,0:17:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...she was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And at your hand, Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what is this all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the rope mark on Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.54,0:17:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part of it goes inside the wetsuit, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.45,0:17:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is because in order to make it look like an accident, after murdering her with the leash, you put a wetsuit on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:18:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a sec, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.12,0:18:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know too, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.09,0:18:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need strength to put on a wetsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.06,0:18:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Nagisa was dead, even if it's a bad example, she'd be like jelly{konjak;kon'nyaku} and not be able to stand up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.68,0:18:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How're you saying I got Nagisa into a wetsuit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then shall we try an experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakata, you're dead. Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! You're right, his foot came through without needing much strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.00,0:18:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the other one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting plastic bags on her feet reduces the friction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the bin Ran brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.80,0:18:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are traces of a pedicure in the plastic bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.57,0:18:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They should match with Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he put a wetsuit on the corpse, then went offshore on a rubber boat to dump her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then in the morning, the corpse would have washed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.27,0:19:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.39,0:19:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When am I supposed to have taken a rubber boat out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday evening, or at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.15,0:19:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-pressure front had come and the seas were very rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rubber boat would've been capsized.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this morning, when the high pressure front had left and the waves had calmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.23,0:19:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boat would be heavy with Nagisa in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there marks anywhere on the beach from a boat being dragged?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa went surfing on stormy seas\Nyesterday evening and died doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.61,0:19:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this morning she washed ashore on the beach here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certainly, when we discovered Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there were no footprints or anything on this wide beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it seemed that she'd been washed ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you looked at the plastic model on that shelf
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.87,0:19:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and thought up the trick to this crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plastic model?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.99,0:20:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.28,0:20:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A crane. By extending the boom,\Nfastening the rope to the deceased,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.64,0:20:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then swinging it left and right like the pendulum in a clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.41,0:20:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and letting go when the reaction is large enou—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.00,0:20:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the deceased flew through the sky and landed in the sea, leaving no footprints on the beach. How's that, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.91,0:20:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.12,0:20:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, after murdering Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou buried her in the sand to hide her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.74,0:20:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The karaoke e-mail was also your doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, this morning, you dug up Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and carried her on your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.65,0:20:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But that'd be the weight of two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.52,0:20:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There'd be footprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used a certain thing so that footprints would not be left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:57.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking a hint from the machine's crawler.{sign: Crawler}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.23,0:21:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you put these together to make a loop, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.20,0:21:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on your back, you went inside and moved along the beach, left Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} behind and then returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.63,0:21:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was that? Did I miss anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.62,0:21:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened yesterday, after Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s group{-tachi} had left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa... She said this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow morning, I'm meeting\Nsomeone under the lone pine tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.50,0:21:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it works out, I'm sending you a divorce notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.05,0:21:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won't you reconsider?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.52,0:21:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, the world is ruled by looks and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.50,0:21:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.19,0:22:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa had married me for my money... Just for my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.27,0:23:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, the last 100 meter straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.02,0:23:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tawāru Gītaka's Anjō-no-Yamagawa's being followed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.47,0:23:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.31,0:23:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Run! Run! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.97,0:23:53.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Haha... I guess someone who can't ride the waves can't go riding money on horses either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.49,0:23:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:23:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morons,{BAAROU!} I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we travel through time?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.94,0:24:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Serial murders shake Nagasaki of the Bakumatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.96,0:24:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the true identity of the girl who holds the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.46,0:24:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A masterful deduction by Sakamoto Ryōma{name is JP order}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.63,0:24:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: The Nagasaki Mystery Theater (Bakumatsu Case).
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.87,0:24:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Font.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't ride money on a winning horse, and can't ride the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.30,0:24:24.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}bōto
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.30,0:24:24.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}botto
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.30,0:24:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then should I just sit still{botto} on a boat{booto}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.29,0:24:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
